    "path": "src/agent/session",
    "name": "session",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent session runtime and session preview context. session.rs defines Session startup, worker routing, package_message(SessionEvent) -> SessionMessage, and route_session_event; after a host channel connects, spawn_host_worker resets SessionState.context and query_host_preview sends an ExecutionEvent::PreviewQuery using ExecutionSignature::new(TaskId::new(), \"preview\".to_string()), so the preview query keeps a caller-supplied TaskId and lets ExecutionSignature allocate the ExeId without importing ExeId in session.rs. route_session_event stores ExecutionEvent::Preview tools while safely ignoring signed standalone step notifications via SessionEvent::Step(_, _). session_state.rs defines SessionState storage for task queues, shared client/host endpoints, and a StdMutex<SessionContext> initialized with empty task and tool lists. session_context.rs defines SessionContext, which holds task previews and tool previews only. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
